                        <span class="tei-persName"> Isidore, Bishop of
                                <span class="tei-placeName"> Kenneshrin
                            </span></span>
                    </span>
                </span> <a href="/805-50" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><h4>Sex: </h4><p class="indent"><span class="tei-persName">Isidore</span> was male. <a href="/3036-13" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><p class="indent"><span class="tei-persName">Isidore</span> was male. <a href="/3040-23" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><p class="indent"><span class="tei-persName">
                                    Isidore </span> was a male.  <a href="/3107-39" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><p class="indent"><span class="tei-persName">Isidore</span> was male.  <a href="/3099-42" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><p class="indent"><span class="tei-persName">Isidore</span> was male. <a href="/805-51" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><h4>Occupation(s): </h4><p class="indent"><span class="tei-persName">Isidore</span> was Bishop of <span class="tei-placeName"> Chalcis
                                </span>. <a href="/3036-14" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><p class="indent"><span class="tei-persName">Isidore</span> was Bishop of <span class="tei-placeName">Chalcis</span>. <a href="/3040-24" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><p class="indent"><span class="tei-persName">
                                    Isidore </span> was the bishop of <span class="tei-placeName"> Chalcis </span>.
                             <a href="/3107-40" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><p class="indent"><span class="tei-persName">Isidore</span> was a bishop. <a href="/805-52" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p></div><div class="sources"><h3>Relationships</h3><p class="indent">Isidore had
                            ecclesiastical authority over Anonymi 3045. <a href="/3036-16" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><p class="indent">Severus of
                                Antioch had ecclesiastical authority over the bishop(s)
                                Isidore. <a href="/3036-18" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><p class="indent">Isidore had
                            ecclesiastical authority over Cosmas, Polyeuctus and
                                Zeno. <a href="/3036-20" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><p class="indent">Isidore had
                            ecclesiastical authority over Anonymi 3045. <a href="/3036-21" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><p class="indent">Severus of
                                Antioch and Isidore had a
                            professional relationship. <a href="/3040-25" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><p class="indent">
                            Severus and 
                            Isidore 
                            had a friendship. <a href="/3099-44" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><p class="indent">Isidore and
                                Severus of
                                Antioch had a professional relationship. <a href="/3099-45" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><p class="indent">
                            Isidore 
                            was bishop with authority over
                            Silvanus.
                         <a href="/3109-5" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p></div><div class="sources"><h3>Events</h3><p class="indent">Severus
                            desired for Cosmas, Polyeuctus, Zeno, and those who were in conflict with
                                them to come to Antioch because
                                Isidore the bishop of
                                    Chalis had not been present to
                            adjudicate.  <a href="/3036-25" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><hr/><p class="indent">Stephen
                            delivered the order to come to Alexandria to
                                Mare and his
                            men as well as to Isidore, Bishop of Kenneshrin, also in
                            exile.  <a href="/805-49" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><hr/><p class="indent">
                            Sometime before 520
                            Isidore re-ordained deacons whom
                            Severus had already ordained. 
                            Severus did not object to this because 
                            this ordination took place far outside of his jurisdiction. 
                         <a href="/3099-6" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
